--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
No, I was not for forced grouping before the May 8 patch on FV. I like grouping with who I want, when I want, regardless of alignment.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
So much for Roleplaying then  <br>
:<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
OH MY GOD!<br>
<br>
I am soo sick of this attitude! Some of you on this game who profess they are roleplaying have no true comprehension of RP or flexibility in RP.<br>
<br>
Roleplaying is being creative, creating a story and being adaptive and flexible when it comes to interacting with others and how their RP affects your RP and changes your story, sometimes in ways you might not want or expect, but living with those consequences of your actions and the actions of others that you choose to allow to affect you.<br>
<br>
So many of you are focused on the rigid stereotypes and how one race hates another race -- you go up to each other in the game and spit off crap about how much you hate each other, and call this RP, and you do this regardless of backstory, interaction or whatever. <br>
<br>
What if I was an evil druid, a sinister wood elf who followed the path of darkness and worshiped some evil god (despite what I'm saddled with because of alignment restrictions in game?<br>
<br>
I'm serious folks, True RP is what you make of it, stop falling back on the basics and come up with stuff for yourself.<br>
<br>
If Jarana wants to group with whomever, whenever she pleases, how is this not RP? Why shouldn't she be able to if this is part of the way she RP's her character?<br>
<br>
Syluran is a Wood elf druid, follower of Tunare -- but good and evil are not clear cut for her. She embraces neutrality -- both good and evil, seeing that both are necessary for the circle of life. Naturally, the game doesn't let me choose what I want, I have to go with what's given me, but why the heck can't I RP that Syluran sees nothing wrong with adventuring with evil and good people alike? I do, end of story and if you have a problem with it, its your problem. Why would a dark elf have a problem with a druid who isn't a 'good' pristine druid? I don't know. Its up to each individual, but it doesn't make sense to me to make base assumptions based on my character and class and RP with me that way, rather than interacting with me and finding out what she's really like, or setting up an RP story where it is a well known fact that Syluran has these beliefs and acting off of that 'preknowledge'. (There's nothing wrong with saying: And oh, you may know through the grape vine, word of mouth or whatever, that this Syluran person believes this this and this and she is not some pristine goody goody) and becoming more flexible and able to group with me because of her beliefs.<br>
<br>
This is why I have a problem with guilds that enforce grouping restrictions based on stereotypical race/class restrictions, because it does not take RP into account, and the way that the person playing that character might have developed themselves.<br>
<br>
IE examples: Kindredwolf, Shadowknight of Tuanare<br>
Kenludar: Tainted half Tier'dal Druid.<br>
<br>
These are two I can think of. But I'm sure there are more.<br>
<br>
What if I, as Syluran decided to make myself KOS in Kelethin because I wanted to have her slowly decend into the dark side?? <br>
<br>
What if I wanted to say she was 1/4th Tier'dal?<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I'm just ranting, this is one of the reasons I rarely RP with folks because I don't think folks on FV are flexible enough in regards to how they RP without resorting to black and white stereotypes handed down from Verant/Sony.<br>
<br>
(And yes, I know some of you will say: But but, this is the way it is and the way they meant to be, and to those of you I say: Where is your adaptability and flexibility?)<br>
<br>
I hope I don't upset anyone too much. I'm just used to a more flexible RP environment.<br>
<br>
