<br>
Eli will group with good, evil and anything in between, as long as it benefits her at the end of the day. She doesn't fit neatly into either category, I guess she's chaotic neutral really.<br>
<br>
Likewise, I don't have a problem with an evil character who'll kill that druid before they have time to protest &quot;But... I'm evil!&quot;<br>
If they want to play a character who wouldn't accept that typically good races can have a change of heart, then that's the character they're playing.<br>
<br>
That said I do think that at the end of the day, RL comes first and if I were playing an evil character and a good character really needed my help, I would probably drop RP for a short time to help them. PoEli doesn't want to see anyone in RL having a hard time, I know how stressful this game can get.<br>
<br>
And finally, I believe guilds should be able to put whatever restrictions they want on their members. The free choice comes in whether you join that guild or not. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwared>Gwared</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Oxymoronic Pally</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/18/03 12:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1931.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ2 release delayed till 2004...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm serious folks, True RP is what you make of it, stop falling back on the basics and come up with stuff for yourself.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
